    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Springfield House, | Bradford—</placeName>
                    <date>3 Dec. 1868.</date>
                    <salute>Honoured Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I presume you are much plagued by applications for your autograph, and if, by adding one more to the list of your troublesome admirers, you deem it too great a liberty, pray excuse me—but grant my request.</p>
<p>I have long been a great admirer of your genius and ever since I have been a collector of autographs, it has been my ardent wish to have yours.</p>
<p>By conferring upon me this favour, you will greatly oblige,</p>
<p>Yours very faithfully | Frederick Behrens— <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin, Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi> | F.R.S. Etc.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>
        
    
        
